---
description: SvelteKit routes, loaders, actions, endpoints (JavaScript only, legacy Svelte)
globs:
  - "src/routes/**/+*.{svelte,js}"
alwaysApply: true
---

# File roles (JS only)
- UI: `+page.svelte`, `+layout.svelte`
- Universal loaders: `+page.js`, `+layout.js`  (export `load`)
- Server-only loaders: `+page.server.js`, `+layout.server.js`  (export `load`)
- Form actions: define in `+page.server.js` via `export const actions = { ... }`
- API endpoints: `+server.js` (export `GET/POST/...` handlers)

# Mode & events
- **Legacy Svelte (no runes):** use `export let`, `$:` and `on:click` (not `$state/$derived/$effect` or `onclick`)
- Do not convert files to TypeScript or create `.ts` variants

# Env & secrets
- Server-only: `$env/static/private` or `$env/dynamic/private`
- Client-only: `$env/static/public` and **PUBLIC_*** keys
- Never import server env modules into `.svelte`, `+page.js`, or other client code

# UX guidance
- Prefer progressive enhancement with form actions; only add fetch/XHR when needed
- Do not modify `<style>` blocks unless explicitly asked
